  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/commit/95bf73f493dc8458a1d6981493275379197a4bdf\r\n* OS: linux\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): 3.10.8\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe data location of a function's arguments is set to `CALLDATA` for external and internal functions, when it should be `MEMORY` for internal functions. This causes the error message to be misleading.\r\n\r\n```\r\n@internal\r\ndef foo(a: uint256):\r\n    a = 1\r\n```\r\n```\r\nvyper.exceptions.ImmutableViolation: Cannot write to calldata\r\n  contract \"tmp/internal_arg.vy:3\", function \"foo\", line 3:4 \r\n       2 def foo(a: uint256):\r\n  ---> 3     a = 1\r\n  -----------^\r\n       4\r\n```\r\n\r\nh/t @trocher @ptrcarta\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nFill this in if you know how to fix it.\r\n",
